	<key>readme</key>
	<string># Note 

This workflow has been tested on macOS 13.0 and will not work on previous macOS versions. It is possible future changes (whether in macOS 13 or later) will stop this workflow workingâ€”either partially or fully.


# Usage

This workflow lists, in response to the user configurable `syset` keyword, various macOS System Preference panes (which are still called `Preference panes` even under macOS 13) to which I have discovered programable access. When you select the relevant pane from the alphabetical, searchable list simply press &lt;Enter&gt; to display the pane. Note that you can leave a space after the keyword and type the initial letter(s) of the pane you want in order quickly to jump to that pane.

![Open macOS Settings Panes](Screenshot/Screenshot.png)

I have chosen to keep the list of panes in alphabetical orderâ€”rather than allowing Alfred to sort them based on usageâ€”as they seem to me easier to browse in that order. If you feel there are too many panes listed by all means delete from the list filter those you do not wish to see.

# Note

The `Mouse`, `Game Controller` and `VPN` panes will not appear unless and until you have connected to one of those relevant devices.


# Acknowledgment

I am indebted to comments on [this Github post](https://gist.github.com/rmcdongit/f66ff91e0dad78d4d6346a75ded4b751?permalink_comment_id=4258811) for enabling me to find identifiers for various Preference panes.

---

**Version 1.1** 26/10/2022: added two further panes (`General` and `Passwords`) and updated Placeholder Title and Placeholder Subtext in workflow.

**Version 1.2** 26/10/2022: updated name of workflow and improved workflow icon.

**Version 1.21** 27/10/2022: small correction to Placeholder Title in workflow.

**Version 1.3** 02/11/2022: added nine new panes (`About`, `Desktop &amp; Dock`, `Extensions`, `Family`, `Game Centre`, `Game Controllers`, `Mouse`, `Transfer or Reset`, and `VPN`) and icons (with credit to @vitorgalvao). Updates to this configuration file.

**Version 1.4** 23/12/2022: add new iCloud pane and added screenshot to User Configuration.

**Version 1.5** 05/01/2023: updated bundle identifier.</string>
